ell%3C%2Fa%3E%20precipitously%20by%20two-thirds%20from%201930%20to%201932.%20A%20rice%20shortage%20caused%20by%20flooding%20and%20limited%20production%20only%20exacerbated%20the%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20turned%20against%20the%20monarchy.%20In%201932%2C%20an%20army%20officer%20called%20Plaek%20Phibunsongkhram%2C%20who%20founded%20the%20radical%20People's%20Party%20five%20years%20earlier%2C%20helped%20lead%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.economist.com%2Fasia%2F1932%2F07%2F02%2Frevolution-in-siam%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecoup%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20the%20Siam%20monarchy.%20Phibun%2C%20as%20the%20officer%20was%20called%2C%20took%20power%20as%20dictator%20in%201938.%20One%20year%20later%2C%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.historytoday.com%2Farchive%2Fmonths-past%2Fsiam-becomes-thailand%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echanged%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20country's%20name%20to%20Thailand%20as%20a%20sign%20of%20modernizing%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20address%20the%20economic%20crisis%2C%20the%20Thai%20government%20under%20Phibun%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fqz.com%2Fquartzy%2F1617172%2Fthailands-beloved-pad-thai-dish-has-a-strange-political-history%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epromoted%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20consumption%20of%20rice%20noodles%2C%20which%20use%20less%20grain%20than%20a%20bowl%20of%20rice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22948%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Plaek%20Phibunsongkhram%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657a1f3c0ec98e92f74f2e15%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22711%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPlaek%20Phibunsongkhram%20became%20prime%20minister%20of%20Thailand%20after%20leading%20a%20military%20coup.%3Cp%3EPublic%20Domain%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPad%20thai%20was%20not%20just%20a%20solution%20to%20an%20agricultural%20crisis.%20Phibun%20sought%20to%20strengthen%20Thailand%20and%20its%20global%20image%2C%20and%20so%20mandated%20the%20creation%20of%20a%20national%20dish.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tastingtable.com%2F1067125%2Fthe-dictator-who-gave-pad-thai-its-name%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esome%20accounts%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20government%20held%20a%20competition%20to%20determine%20a%20national%20noodle%20dish.%20Others%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scmp.com%2Flifestyle%2Ffood-drink%2Farticle%2F3007657%2Fhistory-pad-thai-how-stir-fried-noodle-dish-was-invented-thai%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclaim%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Phibun%20picked%20pad%20thai%20because%20it%20was%20his%20favorite%20version%20of%20a%20noodle%20his%20housekeeper%20made.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPad%20thai%20was%20promoted%20across%20Thailand%20under%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F20062726%3Fread-now%3D1%26seq%3D3%23page_scan_tab_contents%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eslogan%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3Bnoodle%20is%20your%20lunch%2C%26quot%3B%20telling%20residents%20that%20consuming%20pad%20thai%20was%20a%20patriotic%20act%20that%20helped%20with%20the%20war%20effort.%20Promoting%20pad%20thai%20was%20a%20part%20of%20a%20larger%20nation-building%20propaganda%20campaign%20that%20hoped%20to%20strengthen%20Thai%20culture%20globally%20and%20cement%20Phibun's%20status%20as%20leader.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20government's%20push%20to%20make%20pad%20thai%20global%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20Thailand%2C%20pad%20thai%20entered%20the%20international%20food%20scene%20via%20gastrodiplomacy%2C%20which%20is%20when%20a%20country%20uses%20food%20as%20a%20way%20to%20gain%20global%20influence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202002%2C%20the%20Thai%20government%20pushed%20a%20campaign%20to%20increase%20the%20number%20of%20Thai%20restaurants%20around%20the%20world.%20Through%20the%20%26quot%3BGlobal%20Thai%26quot%3B%20program%2C%20the%20government%20offered%20loans%20to%20Thai%20nationals%20who%20wanted%20to%20open%20restaurants%20abroad%20and%20arranged%20meetings%20between%20Thai%20and%20foreign%20business%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20campaign%20was%20a%20success.%20The%20number%20of%20Thai%20restaurants%20abroad%20went%20from%205%2C500%20at%20the%20time%20of%20the%20program's%20launch%20to%20more%20than%2015%2C000%20as%20of%202018%2C%20Vice%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vice.com%2Fen%2Farticle%2Fpaxadz%2Fthe-surprising-reason-that-there-are-so-many-thai-restaurants-in-america%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20countries%20like%20South%20Korea%2C%20Taiwan%2C%20and%20Peru%20have%20since%20followed%20suit%2C%20establishing%20their%20own%20initiatives%20to%20expand%20their%20global%20culinary%20footprint.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpad-thai-food-history-thailand-government-propaganda-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702816441000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657a1f757a3c8094d5dcb96f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpad-thai-food-history-thailand-government-propaganda-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22After%20a%20coup%20in%20the%201930s%2C%20a%20Thai%20dictator%20called%20for%20the%20creation%20of%20a%20national%20dish%20to%20address%20a%20rice%20shortage%20and%20build%20the%20country's%20identity.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Yoonji%20Han)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A19%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpad-thai-food-history-thailand-government-propaganda-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Iyer's%20bat%20goes%20flying%20to%20square-leg%20after%20losing%20grip%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702816433000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-106065484%2Cimgsize-55522.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fsports%2Fcricket%2Findia-in-south-africa%2F1st-odi-shreyas-iyers-bat-goes-flying-to-square-leg-after-losing-grip%2Farticleshow%2F106065490.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Witnessing%20a%20cricket%20ball%20ascend%20into%20the%20air%20is%20a%20familiar%20scene%2C%20but%20the%20sight%20of%20a%20flying%20bat%20adds%20an%20uncommon%20spectacle%20to%20the%20game.%20Fans%20experienced%20this%20unusual%20occurrence%20during%20the%20inaugural%20India-South%20Africa%20ODI%20in%20Johannesburg%20on%20Sunday.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20SPORTS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fsports%2Fcricket%2Findia-in-south-africa%2F1st-odi-shreyas-iyers-bat-goes-flying-to-square-leg-after-losing-grip%2Farticleshow%2F106065490.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22An%20Escapist%20Outlet%3A%20The%20Rise%20of%20Hyper-Masculinity%20in%20Indian%20Cinema%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F17135744%2Fimage-1615.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMadness%20is%20the%20most%20disgraceful%20thing%20that%20can%20overtake%20a%20wild%20creature.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Rudyard%20Kipling%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Jungle%20Book%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20often%20said%20that%20cinema%20acts%20as%20a%20mirror%20to%20the%20society%20we%20live%20in.%20At%20times%2C%20it%20depicts%20issues%20faced%20by%20society%2C%20and%20sometimes%2C%20it%20chooses%20to%20escape%20from%20reality%2C%20taking%20the%20viewer%20to%20an%20imagined%20territory.%20It%20is%20difficult%20to%20identify%20when%20society%20is%20influenced%20by%20cinema%20or%20vice%20versa.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFilms%20depict%20a%20complex%20society%20with%20numerous%20cultures%2C%20identities%2C%20and%20issues%20in%20various%20ways.%20Sometimes%2C%20these%20representations%20raise%20important%20questions.%20In%20recent%20times%2C%20films%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fkabir-singh-movie-review%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EKabir%20Singh%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20(2019)%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fanimal-sandeep-reddy-vangas-crude-and-beastly-assault-on-sense-and-sensibility%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAnimal%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20(2023)%20attracted%20the%20public%20as%20well%20as%20scholarly%20scrutiny%20regarding%20the%20depiction%20and%20politics%20of%20gender%20in%20Indian%20cinema.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20recent%20interview%2C%20actor%20Naseeruddin%20Shah%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EMardon%20ki%20insecurity%20badh%20rahi%20hai%2C%20isiliye%20ab%20aur%20zyada%20zor%20diya%20jaa%20raha%20hai%20hyper%20masculinity%20ko%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%20(the%20insecurities%20of%20men%20are%20increasing%20and%20that%20is%20why%20there%20is%20a%20push%20for%20hyper-masculinity.)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndian%20society%20is%20patriarchal%2C%20and%20the%20Hindi%20film%20industry%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20is%20a%20male-dominated%20industry%2C%20where%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20technical%20crew%2C%20including%20filmmakers%20and%20producers%2C%20are%20male.%20The%20%E2%80%98male%20gaze%E2%80%99%20dictates%20how%20the%20interplay%20and%20politics%20of%20gender%20are%20represented%20in%20our%20cinema.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20student%20of%20history%2C%20my%20work%20allows%20me%20to%20go%20back%20in%20time%20to%20see%20how%20the%20conception%20and%20representation%20of%20masculinity%20has%20evolved%20over%20the%20years.%20When%20I%20think%20of%20films%20like%20%3Cem%3EAnimal%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20%3Cem%3EKabir%20Singh%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20I%20often%20compare%20them%20with%20the%20image%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98angry%20young%20man%E2%80%99%20that%20emerged%20in%20the%201970s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fprasanth-vijays-film-daayam-unravels-keralas-gender-paradox-amidst-grief-and-patriarchy%5C%22%3EPrasanth%20Vijay%E2%80%99s%20Film%20%E2%80%98Daayam%E2%80%99%20Unravels%20Kerala%E2%80%99s%20Gender%20Paradox%20Amidst%20Grief%20and%20Patriarchy%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EExpressions%20of%20anger%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20angry%20young%20man%20was%20violent%20but%2C%20like%20Robin%20Hood%2C%20a%20friend%20of%20the%20poor%20and%20an%20enemy%20of%20the%20rich.%20The%20figure%20of%20the%20angry%20young%20man%20was%20essentially%20anti-establishment%20and%20stood%20for%20the%20welfare%20of%20the%20poor.%20Similar%20to%20Amitabh%20Bachchan%2C%20Naseeruddin%20Shah%20is%20depicted%20in%20art%20house%20films%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.imdb.com%2Ftitle%2Ftt0080343%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAlbert%20Pinto%20Ko%20Gussa%20Kyon%20Aata%20Hai%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20(1980)%20by%20Saeed%20Akhtar%20Mirza%20as%20a%20young%20man%20frustrated%20with%20the%20system%20but%20non-violent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrakash%20Mehra%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EZanjeer%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1973)%20created%20the%20image%20of%20the%20angry%20young%20man%20played%20by%20Amitabh%20Bachchan.%20The%201970s%20were%20more%20turbulent%20and%20testing%20than%20any%20other%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20history%2C%20characterised%20by%20increasing%20unemployment%2C%20poverty%2C%20and%20political%20violence.%20It%20was%20the%20time%20when%2C%20on%20one%20side%2C%20the%20Indian%20armed%20forces%20had%20just%20emerged%20victorious%20in%20the%20Bangladesh%20Liberation%20War%20against%20Pakistan%2C%20and%20on%20the%20other%20side%2C%20the%20daughter%20of%20independent%20India%E2%80%99s%20first%20Prime%20Minister%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%2C%20Indira%20Gandhi%2C%20was%20voted%20in.%20The%20evocative%20slogan%20of%20the%20decade%20was%2C%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%98Indira%20Lao%2C%20Garibi%20Hatao%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Elect%20Indira%2C%20Eradicate%20Poverty).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20terrible%20drought%20in%20East%20India%20in%20the%20mid-1960s%20impeded%20India%E2%80%99s%20development%20and%20aggravated%20poverty%2C%20resulting%20in%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20increased%20reliance%20on%20western%20powers%20for%20aid.%20The%201970s%20witnessed%20the%20hollowness%20of%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%98Garibi%20Hatao%20(Eradicate%20Poverty)%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%20slogan%2C%20juxtaposed%20against%20the%20harsh%20realities%20of%20daily%20life%2C%20marked%20by%20inflation%2C%20escalating%20unemployment%2C%20and%20pervasive%20political%20and%20financial%20corruption.%20Indifference%20towards%20the%20burgeoning%20student%20movements%20nationwide%20further%20fueled%20a%20sense%20of%20helplessness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20common%20man%20was%20disillusioned%20and%20angry%20with%20the%20system%2C%20and%20at%20that%20time%2C%20emerged%20the%20figure%20of%20Inspector%20Vijay%20Khanna%20(played%20by%20Bachchan).%20This%20film%20paved%20the%20way%20for%20a%20new%20kind%20of%20hero%20%E2%80%93%20a%20brooding%2C%20angry%2C%20despondent%20Bachchan%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20the%20romantic%2C%20charming%20Rajesh%20Khanna%20or%20Dev%20Anand.%20The%20%E2%80%98angry%20man%E2%80%99%20persona%20consciously%20reshaped%20notions%20of%20masculinity%2C%20stardom%2C%20and%20political%20discourse%20on%20the%20screen%2C%20leaving%20an%20indelible%20impact%20on%20subsequent%20developments%20in%20cinema.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20Bachchan%E2%80%99s%20Vijay%20Khanna%20was%20to%20commercial%20cinema%2C%20Naseeruddin%20Shah%20and%20Om%20Puri%20were%20to%20art%20house%20cinema.%20Both%20of%20them%20were%20considered%20to%20be%20the%20best%20of%20their%20time.%20They%20immortalized%20characters%20like%20Albert%20Pinto%20from%20Saeed%20Akhtar%20Mirza%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EAlbert%20Pinto%20Ko%20Gussa%20Kyon%20Aata%20Hai%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20Bhiku%20Lahanya%20from%20Govind%20Nihalani%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EAakrosh%3C%2Fem%3E%20during%20the%201980s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2080s%20were%20arguably%20a%20lost%20decade%2C%20with%20Indira%20Gandhi%20pursuing%20her%20gambits%20of%20nationalising%20banks%20and%20loan%20melas%20when%20she%20should%20have%20been%20ushering%20in%20economic%20reforms%20and%20deregulation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20movie%3Cem%3E%20Albert%20Pinto%20ko%20Gussa%20Kyon%20Aata%20Hai%3F%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20central%20themes%20of%20the%20narrative%20revolve%20around%20Pinto%E2%80%99s%20struggle%20to%20determine%20his%20life%E2%80%99s%20purpose%20beyond%20repairing%20expensive%20cars%20for%20affluent%20clients%20at%20the%20garage.%20Pinto%E2%80%99s%20lack%20of%20awareness%20regarding%20the%20social%20and%20political%20dimensions%20affecting%20his%20family%20leads%20to%20the%20imprisonment%20of%20his%20unemployed%20younger%20brother%2C%20exploited%20by%20local%20criminal%20elements.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInitially%2C%20Pinto%E2%80%99s%20anger%20seems%20rooted%20in%20selfishness%2C%20but%20it%20transforms%2C%20symbolising%20a%20broader%20discontent.%20This%20discontent%20is%20reflective%20of%20the%20imminent%20expression%20by%20real%20Mumbai%20textile%20workers%2C%20embodied%20in%20the%20politically%20active%20yet%20defiant%20figure%20of%20his%20father.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20film%20unfolds%2C%20witnessing%20his%20brother%E2%80%99s%20incarceration%2C%20his%20father%E2%80%99s%20loss%20of%20dignity%2C%20and%20the%20company%E2%80%99s%20malicious%20attempts%20to%20discredit%20the%20workers%E2%80%99%20union%20and%20their%20right%20to%20strike%2C%20Pinto%20redirects%20his%20anger%20toward%20a%20more%20fitting%20target%20%E2%80%93%20the%20political%20and%20economic%20elite.%20This%20pivotal%20moment%20is%20captured%20in%20a%20cinema%20setting%2C%20with%20Pinto%20challenging%20the%20political%20address%20of%20the%20company%20management.%20Shouting%20at%20the%20cinema%20screen%2C%20Pinto%20faces%20opposition%20from%20a%20disgruntled%20audience%2C%20and%20Mirza%20subverts%20the%20concept%20of%20political%20acquiescence%20by%20implicating%20the%20broader%20society%20and%20empowering%20Pinto.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECharacters%20like%20Albert%20Pinto%20and%20Vijay%20Khanna%20emerged%20as%20compelling%20figures%2C%20raising%20thought-provoking%20questions%20through%20their%20expressions%20of%20anger%2C%20which%20symbolically%20represented%20a%20more%20profound%20discontent.%20Their%20narratives%20served%20as%20a%20lens%20through%20which%20the%20audience%20could%20analyse%20and%20comment%20on%20the%20intricate%20social%20and%20political%20landscapes%20prevalent%20during%20the%20tumultuous%20decades%20of%20the%201970s%20and%2080s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fkg-george-film-maker-tribute%5C%22%3EK.G.%20George%20Was%20a%20Chronicler%20of%20Society%E2%80%99s%20Patriarchal%20Morality%20and%20Maker%20of%20Thoughtful%20Films%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20present%20cinematic%20landscape%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFast-forward%20to%20the%20present%20cinematic%20landscape%2C%20and%20a%20disconcerting%20pattern%20reemerges%20%E2%80%93%20women%20are%20once%20again%20relegated%20to%20peripheral%20roles%2C%20their%20significance%20measured%20solely%20by%20their%20contributions%20to%20the%20male%20character%E2%80%99s%20storyline.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFilm%20critic%20Anna%20M.M.%20Vetticad%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.firstpost.com%2Fentertainment%2Fthe-pan-india-triumph-of-pushpa-the-rise-united-we-stand-in-our-patriarchy-and-misogyny-10371881.html%5C%22%3Edelves%20into%20this%20issue%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20context%20of%20Pushpa%2C%20elucidating%20how%2C%20in%20a%20contemporary%20India%20marked%20by%20religious%20bigotry%2C%20language%20chauvinism%2C%20and%20caste%20divisions%2C%20potential%20unifying%20factors%20encompass%20misogyny%2C%20patriarchy%2C%20crass%20female%20objectification%2C%20and%20a%20pervasive%20desire%20to%20control%20or%20own%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20historical%20examination%20of%20commercial%20cinema%20reveals%20a%20recurrent%20portrayal%20of%20